verses.verse: He rules by His power forever; His eyes observe the nations; Do not let the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah
Oh, bless our God, you peoples! And make the voice of His praise to be heard,
Who keeps our soul among the living, And does not allow our feet to be moved.
For (Job 23:10; Ps. 17:3) You, O God, have tested us; ((Is. 48:10; Zech. 13:9; Mal. 3:3; 1 Pet. 1:7)) You have refined us as silver is refined.
(Lam. 1:13; Ezek. 12:13) You brought us into the net; You laid affliction on our backs.
(Is. 51:23) You have caused men to ride over our heads; (Is. 43:2) We went through fire and through water; But You brought us out to rich fulfillment.
(Ps. 100:4; 116:14, 17-19) I will go into Your house with burnt offerings; ((Eccl. 5:4)) I will pay You my vows,
